        GUIDES_COUPLE_REPORT_COACHING_TITLE: "<h3>Your Coach, Mark F.</h3><p>We selected Mark for you based on your personality.</p>",
        GUIDES_COUPLE_REPORT_COACHING_DESC: "<p>You've read the guide. You've talked it through with your partner. But for some reason, you're still stuck. For better or worse, that's fairly common. It's not that you're bad at all this - it's just that when you're so close to the problems it can be hard to get the perspective needed to make progress.</p><p>That's why we offer coaching.</p><p>Hi, I'm Mark, your coach. I've coached more than 12,000 people over 30 years. Helping people improve their relationships has been my life's work.</p><p>Because of Interpersonality, I'm now able to help most couples completely turn around their relationships, usually in just a few sessions - even when it seems like all is lost. I know this is possible, because it saved my own relationship.</p><p>This <u>isn't</u> couples therapy. I'm not going to dig into your childhood or ask you to process old emotions. It's not necessary. I won't try to change you, and I won't try to change your partner.</p><p>Instead, I'll help fix the <strong>dynamics</strong> between the two of you.</p><p>Imagine your relationship is a bridge between two cities. Each city has its complexity, its stories, its nice neighborhoods and its rougher areas.</p><p>Therapy is like doing massive renovations on each city - and then hoping that the bridge improves as a side effect. It takes years, and it might not work.</p><p>Coaching with Interpersonality, on the other hand, is like just fixing up the bridge. Add a few support beams, remove the rust, improve the traffic flow a bit.</p><p><strong>Which makes more sense to you?</strong></p><p>Coaching is just $149 per hour. Most couples need just a few hours, ever.</p><p>If you knew for sure that just a few sessions of coaching could save your relationship, you'd want my help.</p><p>Now here's the thing. I know you don't know me. And the world is full of charlatans who promise the world but can't deliver.</p><p><strong>That's why I want you to have your first hour of coaching with me <u>before</u> you decide if you want to pay for it.</strong></p><p>Schedule a session on my calendar below. Coaching happens over a video call on Zoom, Skype, or Google Meet, whichever you are more comfortable with. Bring your partner for the session. Sit on your couch, at the dining table, wherever you prefer.</p><p>Before our first session, you don't pay anything. We won't bill your card ($149, for one hour) until the day after our session.</p><p>If for any reason you didn't think it was worth your time, just send an email to <a href=\"mailto:support@interpersonality.com\">support@interpersonality.com</a> within 24 hours, and we won't charge you. If you aren't happy, you won't pay a dime. Sound reasonable?</p><p>Schedule a session now:</p>",
        GUIDES_COUPLE_REPORT_COACHING_DESC_1: "<div className=\"gray-block\"><h3>How does this work?</h3><p>Calls with your coach are $149 per hour.</p><p>For your first session, we will charge your payment method on file the day after the session, unless you email us at <a href=\"mailto:support@interpersonality.com\">support@interpersonality.com</a> within 24 hours of the session if you are not happy with it.</p><p>For any additional sessions, we will charge your payment method on file the day before the session. You don't need to do anything, just schedule your session and you're done!</p><p><strong>Improving your relationship is one of the best investments you'll ever make.</strong> If you aren't delighted with your coach, we offer a 30-day, 100% money-back guarantee for your most recent session.</p><p>If you need to cancel a session, please do so 2 days in advance. You can do sessions alone or with your partner.</p><p>You can schedule these sessions whenever you'd like, using your coach's schedule above. There is no limit on the number of sessions you can have. If you're unsure how many sessions you'll need, your coach will help.</p></div><div className=\"text-small\"></div>",
        GUIDES_COUPLE_REPORT_WHAT_NEXT_P1:"<p>Has leÃ­do la guÃ­a. Tu pareja ha leÃ­do la guÃ­a.</p><p>Â¿Que sigue?</p><p>Es hora de tener algunas conversaciones con tu pareja al respecto. AquÃ­ es donde comienza el verdadero cambio.</p><p>En esta pÃ¡gina, te daremos algunos consejos sobre como hablar mejor las cosas. Estos consejos ya han sido puestos a prueba antes y garantizarÃ¡n que estas conversaciones tengan el mayor impacto positivo posible en su relaciÃ³n.</p><p>Hemos trazado tres tipos distintos de conversaciones a tener:<ol className='content_ol one'><li>Hablar sobre el conflicto en sÃ­ - sus estilos de conflicto y como manejar el conflicto juntos. Esto viene primero por una razÃ³n.</li><li>Hablar del resto de la guÃ­a - Vida emocional, Estilo de vida, SueÃ±os y metas. Esperen primero hasta tener la conversaciÃ³n sobre el conflicto antes de tener esta conversaciÃ³n.</li><li>Hablar acerca de los conflictos difÃ­ciles que ustedes puedan tener.</li></ol>",
